x4freetext: -NUCLEAR STRUCTURE OF LU-176 AND ITS ASTROPHYSICAL
CONSEQUENCES. I. LEVEL SCHEME OF LU-176.
HIGH FLUX REACTOR AT ILL, GRENOBLE.
THE SAMPLES WERE EXPOSED TO THE THERMAL NEUTRON
FLUX OF 5.5E+14 NEUTRONS/CM2/SEC IN THE CENTRAL POSI-
TION OF THE REACTOR.
.THERMAL NEUTRON SPECTRUM.
.THE NEUTRON CAPTURE IN LU-175 WAS INVESTIGATED USING A
30 MG TARGET OF LU2O3, ENRICHED TO 99.8 PERCENT IN
LU-175. BECAUSE OF THE LARGE CAPTURE CROSS SECTION OF
LU-176, THE REMAINING 0.2 PERCENT CAUSES A SIGNIFICANT
BACKGROUND, AND THEREFORE A SECOND MEASUREMENT WAS
PERFORMED WITH A TARGET ENRICHED TO 27.1 PERCENT IN
IN-BEAM GAMMA SPECTROSCOPY.
.THE GAMMA-RAY SPECTRA WERE DETECTED WITH THE BENT
CRYSTAL SPECTROMETERS GAMS 1 AND GAMS 2/3, WHICH ARE
MOUNTED AT BOTH ENDS OF A HORIZONTAL BEAM LINE THAT
PASSES THE REACTOR CORE TANGENTIALLY. GAMS 1 COVERS
THE ENERGY RANGE UP TO 400 KEV, WHILE GAMS 2/3 WERE
USED ABOVE 200 KEV. THE GAMMA-RAYS WERE DIFFRACTED BY
THE BENT QUARTZ CRYSTALS AND THEN DETECTED BY NAI
SCINTILLATORS IN GAMS 2/3 AND BY A GE DETECTOR IN
GAMS 1. THE RESOLUTION OF GAMS 1 WAS 1.8 AND 2.2 ARC
SECONDS ABOVE AND BELOW 100 KEV, WHILE THE RESOLUTION
OF GAMS 2 AND GAMS 3 WAS 0.59 - 0.62 AND 0.61 - 0.64
ARC SECONDS, RESPECTIVELY. THE RESULTS OBTAINED WITH
GAMS 1 AND GAMS 2/3 WERE COMBINED IN THE ENERGY RANGE
.THE GAMMA-RAY INTENSITIES WERE CORRECTED FOR SELF-
ABSORPTION.
